Stockfish is not linked into, compiled into, or vendored within this
repository. It is used in two places, in both cases as a separate program
communicating over the UCI protocol:

  1. Server-side analysis (packages/worker): executed as a separate
     operating system process. The worker's Docker image downloads the
     pinned official Stockfish release at build time and carries this same
     attribution.

  2. Browser-side live analysis (packages/web): the single-threaded
     WebAssembly build published as the "stockfish" npm package, loaded in a
     dedicated Web Worker. It is copied out of node_modules into
     packages/web/public/engine/ at build time and served as a static asset;
     that directory is gitignored and the binary is not committed here. Its
     GPLv3 license text is copied alongside it and served at
     /engine/Copying.txt, linked from the application's /about page.

  wasm build source: https://github.com/nmrugg/stockfish.js

The chess board piece set is the cburnett set by Colin M.L. Burnett,
tri-licensed GPLv2+ / BSD / GFDL. It is vendored into this repository,
inlined as JSX at packages/web/src/components/pieces.tsx, from the
public/piece/cburnett/ directory of lichess-org/lila.

  Source: https://github.com/lichess-org/lila

The embedded opening book table (packages/shared/src/openings.gen.ts) is
generated from the lichess-org/chess-openings dataset, dedicated to the
public domain under CC0.

  Source: https://github.com/lichess-org/chess-openings
